---
/**
 * /ontology/properties — typed index of object + datatype properties (ADR-0044
 * Phase 4). Reads the SPARQL-derived ontology model (no regex); every property
 * links to its canonical dereferenceable /pdtf page with full domain/range,
 * inverse, constraining shapes and provenance.
 */
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageMeta from '@/components/PageMeta.astro';
import { model } from '@/lib/ontology-model';
import fs from 'node:fs';
import path from 'node:path';

const PUB = path.resolve(process.cwd(), 'public/ontology');
function exists(rel: string): boolean {
  try { return fs.existsSync(path.join(PUB, rel)); } catch { return false; }
}
const names = (refs: { localName: string }[]) => refs.map((r) => r.localName).join(', ');

const objectProps = Object.values(model.objectProperties).sort((a, b) => a.localName.localeCompare(b.localName));
const dataProps = Object.values(model.datatypeProperties).sort((a, b) => a.localName.localeCompare(b.localName));

// Datatype properties grouped by bounded-context module for the collapsible list.
const CTX_ORDER = ['foundation', 'property', 'agent', 'transaction', 'claim', 'governance', 'descriptive'];
const dataByModule = CTX_ORDER
  .map((ctx) => ({ ctx, props: dataProps.filter((p) => p.module === ctx) }))
  .filter((g) => g.props.length > 0);
const dataTotal = dataProps.length;

const PYLODE = { href: '/ontology/tools/pylode/index.html', live: exists('tools/pylode/index.html') };
const WIDOCO = { href: '/ontology/tools/widoco/doc/index-en.html', live: exists('tools/widoco/doc/index-en.html') };
---
<Layout
  title="Properties"
  description="Typed index of the OPDA object and datatype properties — the ~30 object properties in full with domain/range, and the ~226 datatype properties grouped per module — from the SPARQL-derived ontology model. Each property links to its canonical /pdtf page."
>
<PageMeta category="Browse the model" variant="brand" updated="Draft · Updated 2026-06-15" />

  <h1>Properties</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    The OPDA ontology declares <strong>{objectProps.length} object properties</strong> (the relational
    backbone — what links to what) and <strong>{dataTotal} datatype properties</strong> (the literal-valued
    attributes), sourced from the SPARQL-extracted <a href="/ontology/provenance">ontology model</a>.
    <strong>Each property links to its own page</strong> at <code>/pdtf/{'{'}localName{'}'}</code> — with its
    full domain/range, inverse, the SHACL shapes that constrain it, and <code>dct:source</code> provenance.
  </p>

  <div class="callout callout--note">
    <p class="callout__label">domain / range are informative, not enforced</p>
    <p>
      Under the inference / validation boundary (<a href="/ontology/foundation#boundary">ODR-0029</a>),
      <code>rdfs:domain</code> and <code>rdfs:range</code> are <strong>documentation</strong> — a multi-domain
      property reads as a union and is <em>never</em> used to entail types. The actual enforcement is
      value-keyed SHACL (<a href="/ontology/shapes">SHACL shapes</a>). The domain/range shown below is the
      declared documentary intent.
    </p>
  </div>

  <nav class="callout callout--note" aria-label="On this page">
    <p class="callout__label">On this page</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#object">Object properties</a> — {objectProps.length}, listed in full</li>
      <li><a href="#datatype">Datatype properties</a> — {dataTotal}, per module</li>
      <li><a href="#reference">Comparison renderings</a> — pyLODE &amp; WIDOCO</li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <h2 id="object">Object properties <span class="muted">· {objectProps.length}</span></h2>
  <p>
    The relational predicates. Note that several "monetary" predicates in the descriptive module
    (<code>rent</code>, <code>listPrice</code>, <code>currency</code> …) are declared object properties because
    their range is a value-structure or coded scheme rather than a literal.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Domain</th><th>Range</th><th>Module</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {objectProps.map((p) => (
        <tr>
          <td><a href={`/pdtf/${p.id}`}><code>opda:{p.localName}</code></a></td>
          <td>{p.subjects.length ? <code>{names(p.subjects)}</code> : <span class="muted">—</span>}</td>
          <td>{p.objects.length ? <code>{names(p.objects)}</code> : <span class="muted">—</span>}</td>
          <td>{p.module ?? <span class="muted">—</span>}</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="datatype">Datatype properties <span class="muted">· {dataTotal}</span></h2>
  <p>
    The literal-valued attributes — the bulk of the vocabulary, the great majority sourced from PDTF schema
    leaves via <code>dct:source</code>. Grouped by bounded-context module; expand a module for the full list,
    each property linking to its page.
  </p>
  {dataByModule.map((g) => (
    <details>
      <summary><strong>{g.ctx}</strong> <span class="muted">· {g.props.length}</span></summary>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Datatype</th><th>Domain</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          {g.props.map((p) => (
            <tr>
              <td><a href={`/pdtf/${p.id}`}><code>opda:{p.localName}</code></a></td>
              <td>{p.objects.length ? <code>{names(p.objects)}</code> : <span class="muted">—</span>}</td>
              <td>{p.subjects.length ? <code>{names(p.subjects)}</code> : <span class="muted">—</span>}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </details>
  ))}

  <h2 id="reference">Comparison renderings</h2>
  <p>
    The native per-property pages above are the authoritative reference (<a href="/modelling/adr/adr-0044">ADR-0044</a>). The bake-off OWL tools
    remain as comparison extras for the exhaustive axiom view:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>pyLODE</strong> — {PYLODE.live ? <a href={PYLODE.href}>View pyLODE ↗</a> : <span class="pill pill--warn">Pending generation</span>} (best single-file term reference)</li>
    <li><strong>WIDOCO</strong> — {WIDOCO.live ? <a href={WIDOCO.href}>View WIDOCO ↗</a> : <span class="pill pill--warn">Pending generation</span>} (richest publishable shell + VOWL property diagrams)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="related">Related</h2>
  <p>
    See <a href="/ontology/classes">Classes</a> for the subjects these properties attach to,
    <a href="/ontology/vocabularies">Vocabularies (SKOS)</a> for the coded value-spaces many ranges point at,
    <a href="/ontology/datatypes">Datatypes</a> for the literal value-spaces, and
    <a href="/ontology/shapes">SHACL shapes</a> for the constraints that actually enforce them. The namespace
    each term is minted under is on <a href="/ontology/namespaces">Namespaces &amp; prefixes</a>.
    Full index: <a href="/ontology/glossary">Index &amp; glossary</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
